\sum_{i=1}^\infty P(X\geq i)=\sum_{i=1}^\infty\sum_{j=i}^\infty P(X=j).
\sum_{i=1}^\infty\sum_{j=i}^\infty P(X=j)=\sum_{j=1}^\infty\sum _{i=1}^jP(X=j)
\langle i,j\rangle\in\Bbb Z^+\times\Bbb Z^+
j\ge i
\langle i,j\rangle\in\Bbb Z^+\times\Bbb Z^+
i\le j
\sum_{i\ge 1}\sum_{j\ge i}P(X=j)
\sum_{j\ge 1}\sum_{i=1}^jP(X=j)
f(x,y)
y=x
x=1
y=1
\int_1^\infty\int_x^\infty f(x,y)\,dydx=\int_1^\infty\int_1^y f(x,y)\,dxdy\;.
